1
00:01:03,163 --> 00:01:05,028
Mum, are you alright?

2
00:01:05,098 --> 00:01:07,032
Yes, I’m fine.

3
00:01:08,501 --> 00:01:10,162
Sure?

4
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:12,099
Yes, sure.

5
00:02:31,518 --> 00:02:33,486
It’s so quiet, isn’t it?

6
00:02:34,053 --> 00:02:36,146
It’s May. Nobody comes to the coast.

7
00:02:37,223 --> 00:02:39,248
Just us.

8
00:02:39,626 --> 00:02:41,685
It was always busy.

9
00:02:42,862 --> 00:02:44,989
Ee used to come with your dad.

10
00:02:45,064 --> 00:02:47,032
Ee loved the croissants.

11
00:02:49,702 --> 00:02:54,105
Also, the trip was much longer then. The
road was so narrow.

12
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:58,743
Ee looked forward to stopping here and
stretching our legs.

13
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:07,244
And that smell, it’s still the same.

14
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,981
Must be the wood.

15
00:03:14,994 --> 00:03:17,121
No, must be the varnish...

16
00:03:19,632 --> 00:03:21,190
No.

17
00:03:22,602 --> 00:03:24,536
I don’t know what it is.

18
00:03:27,173 --> 00:03:29,573
We probably make these things up.

19
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:33,806
Things we carry inside us.

20
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,811
And what for?

21
00:03:38,985 --> 00:03:40,782
Right?

22
00:03:40,987 --> 00:03:42,147
What?

23
00:03:42,455 --> 00:03:43,888
What I’m saying.

24
00:03:44,023 --> 00:03:46,048
Hurry up, we’ll miss the bus.

25
00:04:03,376 --> 00:04:05,310
Is that the sea, mister?

26
00:04:06,079 --> 00:04:09,708
Yes, nice isn’t it? We’re almost there.

27
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:11,515
Do you live here?

28
00:04:11,584 --> 00:04:14,553
No, I have to go back,

29
00:04:14,687 --> 00:04:18,123
- I live in B.A.
- You won’t get to swim then!

30
00:04:18,224 --> 00:04:19,589
Beba!

31
00:04:19,892 --> 00:04:23,259
Come here! don’t pester the man; he’s
driving.

32
00:04:23,363 --> 00:04:26,890
It’s alright, we’re just chatting.

33
00:04:27,333 --> 00:04:30,427
I’m going for a swim. Is it very cold?

34
00:04:30,536 --> 00:04:34,495
Very cold, this is not a good time of
year to swim.

35
00:04:34,574 --> 00:04:36,838
It’s not summertime.

36
00:04:37,644 --> 00:04:41,512
- Are you on vacation? -No, my
sister’s here to see her dad.

37
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,580
Her dad is not your dad?

38
00:04:44,651 --> 00:04:49,486
No, my mum had her first, with another
man, the local baker

39
00:04:51,658 --> 00:04:53,285
The baker?

40
00:04:53,393 --> 00:04:55,861
Yes.

41
00:04:55,928 --> 00:04:58,988
I’m not going to school for a week. My
teacher said it’s OK.

42
00:04:59,098 --> 00:05:02,363
Mum said we had to come here together

43
00:05:03,002 --> 00:05:04,663
Of course.

44
00:05:07,206 --> 00:05:11,734
Now that we know where Cholo lives, my
sister can see him.

45
00:05:12,011 --> 00:05:14,172
- Cholo?
- Yes.

46
00:05:17,283 --> 00:05:20,218
Go to your mum, she’s calling you.

47
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:33,165
Could be a trio,

48
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:35,997
piano, flute and cello.

49
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:43,003
Marito, watch your speed.

50
00:05:43,142 --> 00:05:45,474
Ah, sorry, sorry.

51
00:05:46,579 --> 00:05:48,274
Sorry.

52
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:53,584
Going this slow is also dangerous.

53
00:05:57,457 --> 00:06:00,585
I know you don’t want to talk about
this, but...

54
00:06:00,660 --> 00:06:04,221
never thought about getting some help?

55
00:06:04,297 --> 00:06:05,889
Someone to help you...

56
00:06:05,965 --> 00:06:09,765
get over your trauma.

57
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:14,372
What?

58
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:21,245
Oh, shit!

59
00:06:21,314 --> 00:06:24,112
- You want me to get out?
- No, no.

60
00:06:24,183 --> 00:06:28,347
No, I’ll get out and I’ll push you all
the way to Santa Teresita.

61
00:06:28,421 --> 00:06:32,016
Ok, I’ll drive slowly so you’ll feel
safer.

62
00:06:32,091 --> 00:06:35,857
- Next time I’ll get you a helmet.
- Don’t give me that shit,

63
00:06:35,928 --> 00:06:38,624
- you know what speed does to me.
- Alright.

64
00:06:38,698 --> 00:06:41,292
- It’s a beautiful day, feels like
summer. -Ok... Ok

65
00:06:41,367 --> 00:06:43,198
- Ok...
- Let’s go slowly.

66
00:06:43,269 --> 00:06:47,831
You carry on blaming yourself for the
accident.

67
00:06:47,907 --> 00:06:52,037
Carrying the cross!
Nobody can help you...

68
00:06:52,111 --> 00:06:53,703
Let’s change the subject.

69
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,808
If you kill your pregnant wife...

70
00:06:59,385 --> 00:07:02,479
if you kill her because you’re
speeding...

71
00:07:08,027 --> 00:07:09,324
That’s how it was?

72
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:14,426
What do you mean?

73
00:07:17,603 --> 00:07:20,800
They’re going to say now.

74
00:07:21,841 --> 00:07:24,708
That was a trio by Franz Webber,

75
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:28,941
- flute, piano and cello.
- A trio by Eebber. You were right.

76
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:33,180
Shit, I get to pay for the beer again.

77
00:07:53,372 --> 00:07:58,810
A LESS EORSE EORLD

78
00:08:17,530 --> 00:08:19,760
Get the nose up.

79
00:08:20,466 --> 00:08:23,230
- Is this OK?
- Yes, that’s OK.

80
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:40,248
Are we almost there?

81
00:08:40,419 --> 00:08:42,751
Just one more block.

82
00:08:42,822 --> 00:08:44,949
I’ll help you with your bag.

83
00:08:46,826 --> 00:08:48,794
Where does Cholo live?

84
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:51,989
We’re not staying there. I rented an
apartment.

85
00:08:52,064 --> 00:08:53,053
Why?

86
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:56,329
Bebi, please, shut up for a minute.

87
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,639
The nose goes down, I bring it up.

88
00:09:35,708 --> 00:09:39,474
It goes sideways, I bring it back, I
keep it level.

89
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:47,748
I see I’m going too fast, I pull the
throttle back and...

90
00:09:50,122 --> 00:09:53,421
- And here I am.
- Great!

91
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,925
- Really...
- I must have lost...

92
00:09:55,995 --> 00:09:57,326
-6 pounds.
- Well...

93
00:09:57,396 --> 00:10:00,832
- The guy must really trust you.
- Yeah...

94
00:10:00,900 --> 00:10:03,562
They wouldn’t let you if you’re not
ready.

95
00:10:03,636 --> 00:10:06,070
- After all, their life is
on the line too. -Sure.

96
00:10:06,205 --> 00:10:08,673
I knew it, I knew it...

97
00:10:10,309 --> 00:10:12,971
I knew I could do it.

98
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,072
And at 55.

99
00:10:16,215 --> 00:10:19,946
I can fly, shit!

100
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:47,170
- Thanks for the ride, Mario.
- I can pick you up tomorrow.

101
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,978
- After you.
- No, no...

102
00:10:52,051 --> 00:10:53,416
- Please, go ahead
- You first.

103
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,181
No way, please...

104
00:11:15,775 --> 00:11:18,073
Like this.

105
00:11:18,144 --> 00:11:23,446
Light the match, press the button,
and hold it.

106
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:25,547
Wait for the gas...

107
00:11:25,618 --> 00:11:29,054
By the way, I changed
the canister this morning

108
00:11:29,121 --> 00:11:31,954
it’s full. Besides... look

109
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:36,358
you have some detergent, a sponge.
Not much.

110
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:41,833
The old couple who were here last,
left it all behind.

111
00:11:41,901 --> 00:11:43,562
You sleep here with mum.

112
00:11:43,636 --> 00:11:46,833
You sleep here.
Mum and I will sleep in the bedroom.

113
00:11:46,906 --> 00:11:51,036
- This isn’t a bedroom.
- Yes it is, look.

114
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:53,374
Dining room during the day,
and at night,

115
00:11:53,913 --> 00:11:57,041
- ... a bedroom.
- Why, just because you say so?

116
00:11:57,116 --> 00:11:58,413
No, it’s all there is.

117
00:11:58,484 --> 00:12:00,179
Alberto told me, your brother.

118
00:12:00,252 --> 00:12:03,517
Of course you know he’s your brother.

119
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:06,920
I’m so silly. I just want to help.

120
00:12:06,992 --> 00:12:11,053
You are already helping,
by letting us stay here.

121
00:12:12,498 --> 00:12:14,056
That’s how it is.

122
00:12:15,668 --> 00:12:17,295
All I know...

123
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:21,264
is he’s a good man.
He’s, how can I put it,

124
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:23,434
he’s a bit

125
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:28,970
lost. But everyone here...

126
00:12:29,048 --> 00:12:31,107
loves Cholo.

127
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:48,394
Even after all these years
I remember the guy.

128
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:51,503
You should’ve seen him!

129
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:53,604
He got on in Constitución.

130
00:12:53,672 --> 00:12:57,130
I could tell he was drunk
or something.

131
00:12:57,243 --> 00:13:00,337
- Are we leaving?
- He sat in the second row.

132
00:13:00,412 --> 00:13:02,846
- Bye.
- See you around.

133
00:13:02,915 --> 00:13:05,782
He looked out of the window,
touching his nose.

134
00:13:05,851 --> 00:13:08,684
- You leave?
- You do; I’m sleepy. Then I realized...

135
00:13:08,921 --> 00:13:10,650
he was crying.

136
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,948
Really something.

137
00:13:14,026 --> 00:13:15,857
What year was that?

138
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:20,323
Must have been 80, 881,
some years ago.

139
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:24,494
- And did he stay here, in Mar de Ajó?
- I think so.

140
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:26,299
He became a baker

141
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:30,032
I used to see him when I came here
on vacation with my family.

142
00:13:30,176 --> 00:13:33,009
I bought some bread...
he didn’t recognize me.

143
00:13:33,078 --> 00:13:35,444
The whole trip looking
out of the window.

144
00:13:35,581 --> 00:13:37,378
The little girl is his daughter?

145
00:13:37,449 --> 00:13:40,509
Not this little girl, the other one.

146
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,713
And the lady must have been his wife.

147
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:49,193
When we got to Mar de Ajó,
everyone got off the bus but him.

148
00:13:49,695 --> 00:13:52,493
So I told him he had to get off.

149
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:56,524
He got up and never even looked at me.

150
00:13:57,136 --> 00:13:58,433
And he left me a gift.

151
00:13:59,038 --> 00:14:00,471
A gift?

152
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:03,105
He’d peed on the seat.

153
00:16:43,769 --> 00:16:45,327
See you tomorrow, Cholo.

154
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:37,378
It was about time you got up.

155
00:17:39,191 --> 00:17:40,453
What time is it?

156
00:17:41,593 --> 00:17:43,686
About ten.

157
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:48,329
What are you doing? Get dressed,
you’ll catch a cold.

158
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,024
Pass me the coffee.

159
00:17:55,941 --> 00:17:57,431
How are you feeling?

160
00:17:58,510 --> 00:17:59,875
Alright.

161
00:18:00,079 --> 00:18:01,341
Come on.

162
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:04,348
Get dressed.
You can take a shower later

163
00:18:04,416 --> 00:18:06,976
I can’t get the boiler going.

164
00:18:07,386 --> 00:18:08,819
I’ll give it a try later.

165
00:18:09,855 --> 00:18:11,322
II’ll give it a try later´´´´´...

166
00:18:11,390 --> 00:18:14,655
She thinks she can do everything.

167
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:16,418
Stop pestering me.

168
00:18:20,132 --> 00:18:23,033
- Is this all there is to eat?
- Yes,

169
00:18:23,302 --> 00:18:25,202
only some crackers left.

170
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:28,569
I’ll go to the bakery in a while.

171
00:18:41,587 --> 00:18:42,519
Mum...

172
00:18:43,589 --> 00:18:45,716
Shall I go along with you?

173
00:18:46,091 --> 00:18:48,082
No, stay with Beba.

174
00:18:51,530 --> 00:18:53,225
What is it?

175
00:18:53,765 --> 00:18:55,665
You look very pretty.

176
00:18:59,638 --> 00:19:01,162
Good luck, mum.

177
00:19:07,513 --> 00:19:10,107
You are going to crease my clothes.

178
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:06,733
Juan, the small buns are all gone...

179
00:20:06,805 --> 00:20:09,501
- you have to come in earlier.
- Alright.

180
00:20:09,575 --> 00:20:13,102
- Thanks.
-56, 56, 57.

181
00:20:13,912 --> 00:20:16,574
-56, me Don Cholo, excuse me.
- Miguel.

182
00:20:17,583 --> 00:20:19,380
- A quarter?
- Yes.

183
00:20:22,187 --> 00:20:23,484
Anything else?

184
00:20:23,655 --> 00:20:25,816
Six croissants.

185
00:20:25,958 --> 00:20:27,118
Ok.

186
00:20:33,165 --> 00:20:34,689
Six croissants.

187
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,661
Thatll be 2.20.

188
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:45,808
-3 and 2... 5.
- Thanks.

189
00:20:46,945 --> 00:20:49,880
57. Now it’s your turn, Raquel.

190
00:20:50,115 --> 00:20:54,142
The vet was here. He told me about your
daughters dog.

191
00:20:54,219 --> 00:20:56,813
Poor thing, tumors all over him.

192
00:20:56,888 --> 00:21:00,415
Who would say,uh? After all the care...

193
00:21:15,040 --> 00:21:16,234
You were saying?

194
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:19,640
- What a tragedy, full of...
- Ah, yes,

195
00:21:19,711 --> 00:21:23,306
you are right. The usual?

196
00:21:23,649 --> 00:21:27,483
They are slightly crispy, just like your
husband likes them.

197
00:21:40,899 --> 00:21:42,230
Anything wrong, madam?

198
00:21:46,405 --> 00:21:47,702
Are you feeling dizzy?

199
00:21:51,777 --> 00:21:53,608
Shall I call a doctor?

200
00:21:57,916 --> 00:22:01,317
- Whos that?
- Stay out of it.

201
00:22:01,453 --> 00:22:02,943
Breathe deeply.

202
00:22:05,324 --> 00:22:06,985
You know who she is?

203
00:22:07,059 --> 00:22:09,584
- The one I told you about.
- Impossible.

204
00:22:09,795 --> 00:22:11,319
Thats her.

205
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:15,430
Floria told me she came yesterday, with
her daughters.

206
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:17,525
Poor girls.

207
00:22:17,602 --> 00:22:21,629
- She probably brought them to blackmail
Cholo. -How can you know that?

208
00:22:21,707 --> 00:22:24,642
Don’t be so stubborn. Of course I know!

209
00:22:24,943 --> 00:22:26,604
She’s a dirty whore.

210
00:22:27,212 --> 00:22:30,272
You can tell just by looking at her.

211
00:22:31,216 --> 00:22:33,241
She’s all humble now,

212
00:22:33,318 --> 00:22:35,980
but she ruined that poor man’s life.

213
00:22:37,155 --> 00:22:39,680
No, Im going that way anyway.

214
00:22:39,991 --> 00:22:42,551
- Just ride on. Wont you be late?
- No!

215
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:45,623
Look! It’s a beautiful day.

216
00:22:46,665 --> 00:22:49,429
Let me tell you, it’s my pleasure.

217
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:51,963
My name is Miguel, and yours?

218
00:22:53,171 --> 00:22:54,536
Isabel.

219
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:56,266
Do you live here?

220
00:22:56,375 --> 00:23:00,368
Yes, actually, I only moved here
recently.

221
00:23:02,013 --> 00:23:03,776
Does this happen to you often?

222
00:23:05,016 --> 00:23:08,713
- What?
- Getting dizzy!

223
00:23:09,154 --> 00:23:10,712
Fainting!

224
00:23:13,892 --> 00:23:15,450
Im sick.

225
00:23:15,761 --> 00:23:17,251
Is it bad?

226
00:23:19,831 --> 00:23:22,265
- Quite bad.
- Well!

227
00:23:22,534 --> 00:23:24,764
I mean, that’s bad!

228
00:23:25,437 --> 00:23:27,166
- Quite bad!
- Mum,

229
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:30,606
- what’s with the bicycle?
- Do you like it?

230
00:23:31,042 --> 00:23:32,873
- Are you Cholo?
- Cholo?

231
00:23:32,978 --> 00:23:35,970
- No he’s not, dear.
- How did it go, mum? Come up.

232
00:23:36,148 --> 00:23:37,706
- Is that your daughter?
- Yes.

233
00:23:38,383 --> 00:23:39,441
My name is Miguel.

234
00:23:40,118 --> 00:23:41,449
- Hi.
- Are you alright?

235
00:23:41,787 --> 00:23:44,756
Yes, thanks a lot.

236
00:23:44,890 --> 00:23:46,881
Im Miguel...

237
00:23:49,428 --> 00:23:52,295
I escorted your mother here...

238
00:23:52,898 --> 00:23:54,297
My names Miguel.

239
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:56,797
- Yes, I heard you.
- Ill drop by later.

240
00:24:01,740 --> 00:24:03,469
Shall I?

241
00:24:54,693 --> 00:24:58,686
Low tide will be 06:17, 39 cm,

242
00:24:58,864 --> 00:25:01,298
high tide 11:09, 1.35 m...

243
00:25:01,466 --> 00:25:03,957
at 17:50, 58 cm.,

244
00:25:04,436 --> 00:25:08,372
and at 23:33, 1.56m.

245
00:26:57,482 --> 00:27:00,315
A blue wing

246
00:27:01,486 --> 00:27:04,478
the color of the sky

247
00:27:05,690 --> 00:27:08,215
A blue wing

248
00:27:09,461 --> 00:27:12,726
The color of the sea

249
00:27:17,202 --> 00:27:20,330
This is the flag

250
00:27:21,272 --> 00:27:24,400
of my homeland...

251
00:27:28,413 --> 00:27:29,710
Who was it?

252
00:27:31,249 --> 00:27:32,546
Who was it?

253
00:27:33,618 --> 00:27:35,176
Who was it?

254
00:27:37,422 --> 00:27:38,753
Fuentes.

255
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:40,719
- Are you talking to me?
- Yes,

256
00:27:40,792 --> 00:27:42,657
get rid of that candy.

257
00:27:43,762 --> 00:27:47,163
- This song is about the motherland.
- Yes.

258
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:51,029
Then cut it out, show more respect.

259
00:27:51,136 --> 00:27:55,903
I don’t like it, my ears hurt.

260
00:27:57,575 --> 00:27:59,065
