01:03:39,081 --> 01:03:41,072
II didn’t know pain could go...

771
01:03:41,150 --> 01:03:46,110
hand in hand with excitement...

772
01:03:46,189 --> 01:03:48,783
- Hey!
- with an urge to hold you...

773
01:03:48,858 --> 01:03:52,089
- and get inside your body to fill you
with passion -No...

774
01:03:52,495 --> 01:03:54,895
- The old man was really something.
- I can’t believe it.

775
01:03:54,964 --> 01:03:59,162
- These are her letters to him.
- Let me see them.

776
01:04:00,002 --> 01:04:01,867
They are so divine.

777
01:04:02,104 --> 01:04:03,935
- Wait!
- What?

778
01:04:04,373 --> 01:04:09,310
- He’s crazy and excited.
- Let me see.

779
01:04:09,412 --> 01:04:11,403
Just give me one... any one of them.

780
01:04:11,581 --> 01:04:12,775
Let me see...

781
01:04:14,050 --> 01:04:16,416
Let me see, let me see...

782
01:04:17,019 --> 01:04:20,011
MMy dear, adorable Arturo´´´´´:::

783
01:04:21,424 --> 01:04:25,155
- That’s nice... although Arturo doesn’t
sound adorable. -Come on.

784
01:04:26,529 --> 01:04:28,554
The old lady has spelling mistakes!

785
01:04:29,265 --> 01:04:32,291
- I think she’s German or something.
- Oh, I see.

786
01:04:32,468 --> 01:04:36,700
Listen.
TThinking about you keeps me going...

787
01:04:36,772 --> 01:04:39,104
you make me believe not everything’s
like this.

788
01:04:39,175 --> 01:04:42,975
What these somnambulist faces tell me,

789
01:04:43,045 --> 01:04:44,876
with which we search...

790
01:04:45,414 --> 01:04:48,315
what we know we’ll never find..

791
01:04:50,786 --> 01:04:53,414
- Leave it, take one of these.
- No, let me carry on.

792
01:04:58,094 --> 01:04:59,686
II don’t want to be here,

793
01:05:00,930 --> 01:05:03,023
to suffer in this search.

794
01:05:03,933 --> 01:05:06,731
Sometimes
I even curse for being a Jew...

795
01:05:07,503 --> 01:05:09,903
for having been born to see all this.

796
01:05:10,940 --> 01:05:14,808
I curse my stupid hope, which is no
longer that but something else:

797
01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:18,077
It’s letting go among so much death.

798
01:05:19,882 --> 01:05:23,010
among so many people
destroyed for nothing.

799
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:25,410
My aunt no longer talks to me.

800
01:05:26,222 --> 01:05:28,918
It’s as if first,
they took her smile away,

801
01:05:29,892 --> 01:05:31,257
then her look,

802
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:34,195
and now even her soul.

803
01:05:35,564 --> 01:05:38,761
Returning to this hell with her looking
for the others,

804
01:05:39,302 --> 01:05:42,237
returning to this destruction where
everybody’s silent,

805
01:05:43,005 --> 01:05:45,496
where nobody explains and looks the
other way,

806
01:05:45,775 --> 01:05:48,266
feigning innocence, trying to forget.

807
01:05:49,612 --> 01:05:51,136
Im afraid, Arturo.

808
01:05:52,081 --> 01:05:53,810
Afraid of losing my faith...

809
01:05:54,717 --> 01:05:56,548
or a reason to live.

810
01:05:57,687 --> 01:06:02,147
Yesterday I got some flowers and stared
at them by the window.

811
01:06:02,792 --> 01:06:04,384
And you know what, my love?

812
01:06:06,429 --> 01:06:10,024
I thanked God I could still feel
something in their beauty,

813
01:06:10,766 --> 01:06:12,233
in their scent,

814
01:06:12,735 --> 01:06:16,330
something so simple yet so wonderful.

815
01:06:17,106 --> 01:06:18,300
And there,

816
01:06:18,908 --> 01:06:22,844
in the miracle of feeling alive,
I saw you, sweetheart.

817
01:06:23,446 --> 01:06:25,311
Your eyes, your warmth

818
01:06:26,515 --> 01:06:27,914
and your kindness.

819
01:06:30,052 --> 01:06:31,610
I need you badly.

820
01:06:32,888 --> 01:06:37,757
I wish the world would learn from you,
so It’s never like this again..

821
01:07:36,018 --> 01:07:37,383
How’s it going?

822
01:07:39,889 --> 01:07:41,356
Aren’t you open in the afternoons?

823
01:07:41,557 --> 01:07:44,321
- Until summertime, only in the morning.
- Yeah.

824
01:07:44,393 --> 01:07:47,191
- No point in opening in the afternoon.
- You’re right. Coming with me?

825
01:07:47,830 --> 01:07:50,856
- Do you have a class?
- Yes, it’s a nice day,

826
01:07:50,933 --> 01:07:54,232
it’s windy.
I called; they said I could go.

827
01:07:54,336 --> 01:07:57,100
Ill take a one hour class
and come back.

828
01:07:57,306 --> 01:08:01,402
But I told Olga we were going fishing.

829
01:08:02,178 --> 01:08:04,874
- What are you looking at?
- Must be expensive:

830
01:08:05,181 --> 01:08:07,513
the flying and buying the fish.

831
01:08:07,583 --> 01:08:10,416
This time, no fish. No way.

832
01:08:10,486 --> 01:08:14,786
Ill say we didn’t catch anything.

833
01:08:14,990 --> 01:08:19,427
- Let her cook a vegetable pie.
- Why don’t you just tell her?

834
01:08:19,495 --> 01:08:22,953
I can’t, leave it. I just can’t.

835
01:08:23,599 --> 01:08:28,502
How do you tell four women
you’re flying at fifty-five?

836
01:08:28,971 --> 01:08:31,371
They’d worry. They’d...

837
01:08:31,907 --> 01:08:35,741
They’d break my legs to keep me from
going. They worry!

838
01:08:51,327 --> 01:08:52,954
- Hello.
- Hello.

839
01:08:53,028 --> 01:08:54,791
- How are you?
- Fine.

840
01:08:54,864 --> 01:08:58,061
- I am... -I know who you are.
Do you want to come in?

841
01:08:59,435 --> 01:09:01,630
I came here last summer

842
01:09:02,404 --> 01:09:05,134
But we’ve known each other
since I was 17.

843
01:09:06,775 --> 01:09:10,871
I came with a guy and we stayed here.

844
01:09:11,247 --> 01:09:14,239
Coca helps out in the summer.
She’s a caretaker off season.

845
01:09:15,751 --> 01:09:18,743
And then it happened and we realized.

846
01:09:19,221 --> 01:09:21,189
To the people in the town,
we’re sisters.

847
01:09:21,423 --> 01:09:24,915
- They all know, but they look
the other way. -Not all of them.

848
01:09:25,594 --> 01:09:28,757
Those who don’t,
it’s because they don’t want to.

849
01:09:28,931 --> 01:09:30,262
That’s something else.

850
01:09:30,633 --> 01:09:31,964
But that’s how it is.

851
01:09:34,003 --> 01:09:35,903
What do you do with Cholo?

852
01:09:36,005 --> 01:09:37,404
You work?

853
01:09:40,009 --> 01:09:41,533
Why do you call him Cholo?

854
01:09:41,877 --> 01:09:43,037
He’s your old man.

855
01:09:45,881 --> 01:09:48,349
Yes, but since he doesn’t know...

856
01:09:49,251 --> 01:09:50,411
Doesn’t know?

857
01:09:51,820 --> 01:09:55,347
That I’m his daughter,
that we’re here with my mum.

858
01:09:58,394 --> 01:09:59,656
What?

859
01:10:00,796 --> 01:10:02,661
You think your dad doesn’t know?

860
01:10:06,735 --> 01:10:07,759
No.

861
01:10:09,572 --> 01:10:10,903
Of course he does.

862
01:10:12,208 --> 01:10:13,675
Your dad saw your mum.

863
01:10:14,710 --> 01:10:17,804
But it’s logical. How do you expect...?

864
01:10:18,847 --> 01:10:22,476
What? Excuse me,
what logic are you talking about?

865
01:10:22,551 --> 01:10:25,748
Whoever comes here,
does so for a reason.

866
01:10:26,589 --> 01:10:28,614
I don’t talk much with your dad, but...

867
01:10:29,658 --> 01:10:31,683
sometimes he just stares at me and...

868
01:10:33,796 --> 01:10:35,730
You know what? Now I understand.

869
01:10:36,899 --> 01:10:38,730
He’s thinking about you.

870
01:10:41,937 --> 01:10:43,427
If I were you,
I’d leave things the way they are.

871
01:10:44,006 --> 01:10:47,169
He’s alright,
he’s a good guy, he’s happy.

872
01:10:50,246 --> 01:10:52,874
Besides, if you push him,
the only thing you’ll achieve...

873
01:10:52,948 --> 01:10:58,716
is he’ll re-live everything,
and he’ll be devastated.

874
01:11:02,558 --> 01:11:05,254
Don’t get upset,
that’s the way it is.

875
01:11:09,198 --> 01:11:10,426
Is it?

876
01:11:11,834 --> 01:11:13,665
Why does it have to be that way?

877
01:11:14,536 --> 01:11:17,198
All we want is to be with him.

878
01:11:17,573 --> 01:11:19,632
We’re not going to hurt him.

879
01:11:20,309 --> 01:11:22,903
But here he invented a past,
better than the one he had.

880
01:11:24,246 --> 01:11:25,907
Better than what?

881
01:11:26,982 --> 01:11:30,713
- You mean better without us?
- Yes.

882
01:11:30,886 --> 01:11:33,980
I know it’s tough. Like we have to
invent we’re sisters.

883
01:11:34,423 --> 01:11:36,983
That’s the way it is. What can I say?

884
01:11:38,961 --> 01:11:41,429
Yes, whatever.

885
01:12:07,189 --> 01:12:11,421
This was a concert in E Major by Pietro
Antonio Locateli...

886
01:12:12,828 --> 01:12:17,765
by the musicians of Sarajevo, directed
by Yanos Pora.

887
01:12:19,668 --> 01:12:22,102
Cholo, let’s play something else.

888
01:12:22,738 --> 01:12:24,831
This is too expensive for me.

889
01:12:25,274 --> 01:12:28,937
It was your idea in the first place,
wasn’t it?

890
01:12:29,144 --> 01:12:32,944
No, well... true, but that’s it. You’re
a genius.

891
01:12:33,082 --> 01:12:36,051
- Me! I keep on paying.
- Yeah, but I come along with you.

892
01:12:36,719 --> 01:12:38,914
- That’s because you’re my friend.
- Of course,

893
01:12:39,121 --> 01:12:41,453
I wouldn’t do it just for a free beer,
would I?

894
01:12:41,523 --> 01:12:43,753
Yes, of course.

895
01:12:44,360 --> 01:12:48,421
- OOf course´´´´´
- But you can’t take criticism.

896
01:12:48,864 --> 01:12:50,832
You’re my only friend.

897
01:12:51,333 --> 01:12:55,497
Do you think I can’t see that you’re
always with me?

898
01:12:55,671 --> 01:12:58,401
You’re also my only friend. Sometimes I
wonder why.

899
01:12:59,575 --> 01:13:02,772
I don’t know, I don’t know why.

900
01:13:03,545 --> 01:13:07,914
Because we love each other we have a
lot in common.

901
01:13:08,050 --> 01:13:11,747
- Think so?
- Yes... I don’t know.

902
01:13:12,888 --> 01:13:14,412
Neither do I.

903
01:13:14,590 --> 01:13:19,220
When I was a kid, maybe eight or nine,
my grandpa sat me on his lap...

904
01:13:19,294 --> 01:13:23,526
stared at me and said: the most
important thing in life are friends.

905
01:13:24,333 --> 01:13:26,767
- Very wise.
- Wise!

906
01:13:27,202 --> 01:13:30,638
It took a lifetime for me understand
that it was bullshit.

907
01:13:30,706 --> 01:13:34,574
The important thing is fighting for your
ideals. When you do,

908
01:13:34,643 --> 01:13:39,580
you lose at least 80º/º of what he said
was important.

909
01:13:39,882 --> 01:13:44,046
That’s a point of view. I think your
grandpa was right.

910
01:13:44,586 --> 01:13:47,384
- You don’t get it, Mario.
- Of course.

911
01:13:47,589 --> 01:13:50,854
When I don’t agree with you, then I
don’t get it?

912
01:13:52,094 --> 01:13:55,586
And don’t give me that shit! What ideals
do you have?

913
01:13:56,098 --> 01:13:58,225
None, that’s why we keep on being
friends.

914
01:13:59,201 --> 01:14:00,793
I want none.

915
01:14:04,206 --> 01:14:06,367
- Watch your speed.
- Yes, yes.

916
01:14:21,790 --> 01:14:22,654
Hello.

917
01:14:23,358 --> 01:14:24,882
The fisherman! Hello.

918
01:14:25,093 --> 01:14:26,720
- How are you, Marcelito?
- Fine.

919
01:14:26,895 --> 01:14:29,227
- What are you playing?
- Just killing time.

920
01:14:30,799 --> 01:14:32,198
Cholos not in.

921
01:14:32,835 --> 01:14:34,132
- Isnt he?
- Do you know when he’ll be back?

922
01:14:34,236 --> 01:14:36,204
He went with Mario to see my dad.

923
01:14:36,805 --> 01:14:39,706
- Where to? -They went flying.
My dad’s the instructor.

924
01:14:40,509 --> 01:14:42,101
He flies planes?

925
01:14:42,411 --> 01:14:44,003
That’s nice.

926
01:14:44,112 --> 01:14:46,273
Come, come in.

927
01:14:53,088 --> 01:14:54,419
- Make yourselves at home.
- Thank you.

928
01:14:54,490 --> 01:14:56,287
I make a great coffee.

929
01:15:02,698 --> 01:15:05,360
Tell me, Marcelito, Cholos house...

930
01:15:05,534 --> 01:15:09,470
- is it like this one?
- Yes, only it’s the other way round,

931
01:15:09,538 --> 01:15:11,904
being across the hallway.

932
01:15:15,644 --> 01:15:17,908
You know what? Bad news.

933
01:15:18,480 --> 01:15:19,742
- What?
- Don’t be mad.

934
01:15:20,115 --> 01:15:22,208
- No
- We’ve run out of coffee.

935
01:15:24,086 --> 01:15:25,678
Don’t worry, dear.

936
01:15:34,096 --> 01:15:35,393
Yes.

937
01:15:43,305 --> 01:15:45,068
Can you help me?

938
01:15:45,607 --> 01:15:47,472
What’s the problem?

939
01:15:47,709 --> 01:15:49,438
Sit down.

940
01:16:04,326 --> 01:16:07,784
- Why do you have so many blank report
cards? -Look,

941
01:16:07,863 --> 01:16:10,354
I will pass, that I can promise.

942
01:16:10,732 --> 01:16:13,963
The thing is I have to fix my marks...

943
01:16:14,069 --> 01:16:16,333
or my dad will go crazy.

944
01:16:17,506 --> 01:16:19,167
What do you want me to do?

945
01:16:19,508 --> 01:16:21,305
I dont know...

946
01:16:21,777 --> 01:16:24,678
you could forge them for me.

947
01:16:30,352 --> 01:16:31,785
Why did they beat us?

948
01:16:33,288 --> 01:16:37,054
Because the British had more
weapons and were more powerful.

949
01:16:38,627 --> 01:16:40,390
Why did they want to kill us?

950
01:16:41,997 --> 01:16:43,897
That’s the way wars are, I don’t know.

951
01:16:46,068 --> 01:16:48,195
What were you talking about?

952
01:16:48,270 --> 01:16:50,568
- Nothing! A surprise!
- What surprise?

953
01:16:50,672 --> 01:16:53,197
Marcelito was showing me his room.

954
01:16:57,879 --> 01:16:58,937
What’s that!

955
01:16:59,081 --> 01:17:00,673
It’s about my father.

956
01:17:01,049 --> 01:17:02,778
He sank a ship.

957
01:17:28,076 --> 01:17:29,873
Mario, this is it.

958
01:17:33,015 --> 01:17:35,813
It’s ready. It’s all yours.

959
01:17:38,220 --> 01:17:40,654
- Come on, Mario.
- No, listen to me.

960
01:17:41,123 --> 01:17:42,454
Lalo, no, listen to me.

961
01:17:42,858 --> 01:17:46,817
You know that I... This is without
warning.

962
01:17:46,995 --> 01:17:50,692
I don’t normally mail a thing like this.
You are ready. Period.

963
01:17:51,400 --> 01:17:54,130
Believe me, Mario. And believe in
yourself.

964
01:17:54,636 --> 01:17:56,604
- Believe in yourself.
- Listen, no, Lalo...

965
01:17:57,105 --> 01:17:58,504
Give me a break.

966
01:17:58,674 --> 01:18:02,474
- Don’t just leave me here.
- Please!

967
01:18:02,678 --> 01:18:06,273
Lalo, I’m sorry... Im sorry...

968
01:18:06,348 --> 01:18:08,782
- I’m sorry to insist. Please,...
- Come on!

969
01:18:08,850 --> 01:18:10,613
Im not too sure about some things.

970
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:13,814
- There are certain details...
- Don’t give me that.

971
01:18:13,889 --> 01:18:17,985
You’re ready. That’s an order. Get up in
there, Mario.

972
01:18:18,193 --> 01:18:20,423
Well be in 1223,

973
01:18:20,495 --> 01:18:21,359
we’ll be on the same frequency.

974
01:18:21,430 --> 01:18:23,295
- Calm down. Calm down.
- What is it?

975
01:18:23,365 --> 01:18:26,232
- Come on.
- What is it? Now it’s my turn;

976
01:18:26,301 --> 01:18:31,364
I have to do it alone. Listen!

977
01:18:31,773 --> 01:18:36,904
- I’m not feeling well, as I told you in
the car. -Again?

978
01:18:36,978 --> 01:18:40,880
Mario, cut the bullshit. You are ready,
just get up in there.

979
01:18:40,949 --> 01:18:45,045
I can’t do it, Cholo! I just can’t. You
know what?

980
01:18:46,054 --> 01:18:49,046
I have diarrhoea, I could see this
coming.

981
01:18:49,357 --> 01:18:50,654
- Another excuse.
- Let’s go.

982
01:18:50,892 --> 01:18:52,757
- Where to?
- Let’s go,

983
01:18:53,462 --> 01:18:55,089
- May I, Fuentes?
- Are you a pilot?

984
01:18:55,397 --> 01:18:57,297
- No, no way.
- In that case,

985
01:18:57,733 --> 01:19:00,361
go ahead. Go for it. Bye.

986
01:19:10,445 --> 01:19:12,743
- Everything OK?
- What the fucks wrong with this?

987
01:19:12,948 --> 01:19:15,143
- What’s up with it?
- It’s stuck.

988
01:19:15,317 --> 01:19:17,376
- Go back, then.
- Ah, that’s it.

989
01:19:19,955 --> 01:19:22,947
Don’t talk to me, I have to
concentrate.

990
01:19:23,158 --> 01:19:25,524
Then shut up and concentrate.

991
01:19:25,861 --> 01:19:29,160
- You’re distracting me!
- Pay attention to what you’re doing!

992
01:19:29,231 --> 01:19:30,425
Im doing so.

993
01:19:30,499 --> 01:19:31,966
Im paying attention, damn it...

994
01:19:33,268 --> 01:19:36,032
Easy, Mario, I have a daughter!

995
01:19:39,207 --> 01:19:40,868
- What was that?
- Pay attention.

996
01:19:44,079 --> 01:19:47,071
- What storm?
- What are you doing?

997
01:19:47,816 --> 01:19:48,976
Please, Mario.

998
01:19:49,050 --> 01:19:51,780
- What...?
- Concentrate!

999
01:19:51,853 --> 01:19:54,754
Concentrate, or we’ll crash!

1000
01:19:55,257 --> 01:19:59,284
- That’s Julian’s palm tree, he brought
it from Entre Ríos. -Pay attention!

1001
01:20:00,128 --> 01:20:04,087
Why don’t you just enjoy it?
Relax, deep breaths.

1002
01:20:05,200 --> 01:20:07,225
Calm down, enjoy it!

1003
01:20:08,436 --> 01:20:09,664
Lalo!

1004
01:20:10,405 --> 01:20:12,066
- Don’t shout!
- Are you sweating?

1005
01:20:12,307 --> 01:20:14,935
Yes, I’m sweating, Mario.

1006
01:20:15,410 --> 01:20:17,139
- You fly it.
- No way!

1007
01:20:17,712 --> 01:20:19,646
- Come on!
- Do you want me to get out?

1008
01:20:19,714 --> 01:20:22,706
- I leave it!
- Cut it out!

1009
01:20:23,652 --> 01:20:26,450
Happy birthday!

